race.comment: DUE CALZINI (7) won easily over a staying trip at Wagga and then came back to the mile freshened at Cootamundra and was beaten a nose heavily bet again. Has an awkward barrier but the in-form Boudvillain stays aboard and the Seib yard is flying. Tough to beat with average luck. TAVOLO (10) peaks off a narrow defeat at Kembla Grange stepping up to this distance. Maps for a soft run and Alysha Collett is a key jockey engagement replacing the 3kg apprentice. She's ready to win. GENETIC FREAK (4) seeks the hat-trick off an all the way win here this grade over 1400m and will be further improved. The ex-Queenslander keeps the handy 3kg claim and has placed 2/4 over this journey. STONECOAT (5) is a leader who was a comfortable 75 winner here two back at the mile. He's been kept on the fresh side off a solid run at Kembla Grange and is sure to give a sight.
